					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://wordcounter.net/blog/2014/05/09/105_make-money-writing.html#comments/12531&quot;&gt;Eryn&lt;/a&gt;.

Most people fail to understand this. To be successful in writing, you need to treat it as a job, not a hobby. Sure, there are exceptions to the rule, but there are also people who make money by winning the lottery. It happens, but it&#039;s not a viable option for the vast majority of people. If you want to make money as a writer, you need to treat writing as a job.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2014/05/09/105_make-money-writing.html#comments/12531">Eryn</a>.</p>
<p>Most people fail to understand this. To be successful in writing, you need to treat it as a job, not a hobby. Sure, there are exceptions to the rule, but there are also people who make money by winning the lottery. It happens, but it&#8217;s not a viable option for the vast majority of people. If you want to make money as a writer, you need to treat writing as a job.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
